<p>it was there that the awful atrocity of cutting breasts off nuns who would not betray the Allies, took place.<br/>The Flemish lady referred to, was in Ypres during the German occupation of that town, &amp; surprised us by remarking that they were not bad on the whole.  Some were beastly &amp; others were good, &amp; on the whole they were not worse than they had expected.  Of course there was a great deal of drinking &amp; drunkenness, but these people evidently expect that from any victorious troops.  I think that three years has been sufficient to make them regard with a <strike>more kindly</strike> less critical eye, what at first must have horrified them</p>
